[10:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Then we have temperature and top P. If you adjust the temperature, if you lower it, it\'s going to be closer to your prompt and the vibe of the prompt. If you raise it, the model is going to take license and kind of add some creativity to what this thing is actually about.'

[10:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The top P is more about the lyrics themselves. The lower you have the low P, the more common the words are that it\'s going to use. The higher you raise it, it\'s going to use some weird vocabulary, but then you run into the'

[10:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'risk of getting nonsense words. Let\'s go ahead and just for fun raise the temperature up on both of these, click on confirm, and let it think about it. I\'ve been flying around the planet since the crack of dawn shooting lovers on the'

[10:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'park bench hiding on a lawn. My shoulders act up and my wings are sore. Again, we have the temperature setting for the styles. So, like with the lyrics, a lower temperature is more consistency, higher is more creative, and top P is more predictable at lower values and crazy time at higher values.'

[10:55] [scene:talk]
